{"type":"message","id":"72f1ea9c","parentId":"c9fad965","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:32:51.114Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_scwey0agvq0a_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4807\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2923\n[file inferred from ACTION] experiments/tic_classifier.ps1\n[mutation proposed] experiments/tic_classifier.ps1\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 083220 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight reveals that the TIC experiment is the critical next step to validate the unified Phase 1/2 hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns in pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"oceanic-shoal","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4807\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2923\n[file inferred from ACTION] experiments/tic_classifier.ps1\n[mutation proposed] experiments/tic_classifier.ps1\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 083220 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight reveals that the TIC experiment is the critical next step to validate the unified Phase 1/2 hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns in pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774355571112}}
{"type":"message","id":"aa6893e8","parentId":"72f1ea9c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:32:51.116Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_scwey0agvq0a_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 082914\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- A key insight has emerged: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - compression and causal discovery are the same problem\r\n- Next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n- Pending: Write PowerShell wrapper, define significance scoring, tune λ, wire to TemporalAttention backend, measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe immediate next action from the goals is:\r\n\"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\"\r\n\r\nThis is the most logical next step. I need to implement a TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant (stable, recurring) vs variant (changing)\r\n3. Uses invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists:\r\n- Pulse logs are at `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n- There's research documentation at `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\r\n\r\nI should create a script that implements the TIC classifier. This would be a PowerShell script since that's the existing infrastructure.\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant (stable) vs variant (changing) patterns\r\n3. Attempts to predict the next pulse based on invariants\r\n4. Measures accuracy against the success criteria\r\n\r\nThis advances the Phase 1 advancement goal directly.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. The pulse logs exist and contain the data needed to test invariant/variant classification and next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic-classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that reads pulse logs, classifies content as invariant vs variant, and attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants. This directly implements the Phase 1 advancement experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env pwsh\r\n# TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$LogCount = 10,\r\n    [int]$PredictionWindow = 3,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- Configuration ---\r\n$SuccessInvariantRate = 0.70  # >70% classification accuracy\r\n$SuccessPredictionRate = 0.60 # >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\n# --- Utilities ---\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    Get-ChildItem -Path $LogPattern -File | \r\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n        Select-Object -First $LogCount\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Parse-PulseContent {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\r\n    # Extract key elements: goals, actions, observations, insights\r\n    $elements = @{\r\n        Timestamp = $content -match '\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}' ? $Matches[0] : \"unknown\"\r\n        Goals = [regex]::Matches($content, '##\\s+(Active|Completed|Pending)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n        Actions = [regex]::Matches($content, '###\\s+[A-Z][^\\n]+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n        Insights = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\d+\\.\\s+\\*\\*[^*]+\\*\\*') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n        Mutations = [regex]::Matches($content, 'file:\\s+([^\\s]+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value }\r\n        Raw = $content\r\n    }\r\n    return $elements\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Compute-Invariants {\r\n    param([array]$PulseElements)\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant: appears in >70% of pulses (stable structure)\r\n    # Variant: appears in <50% of pulses (changing content)\r\n    \r\n    $allGoals = $PulseElements | ForEach-Object { $_.Goals } | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -ge ($PulseElements.Count * 0.7) }\r\n    $allActions = $PulseElements | ForEach-Object { $_.Actions } | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -ge ($PulseElements.Count * 0.7) }\r\n    $allInsights = $PulseElements | ForEach-Object { $_.Insights } | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -ge ($PulseElements.Count * 0.7) }\r\n    $allMutations = $PulseElements | ForEach-Object { $_.Mutations } | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -ge ($PulseElements.Count * 0.5) }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Goals = $allGoals\r\n        Actions = $allActions\r\n        Insights = $allInsights\r\n        Mutations = $allMutations\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Classify-Element {\r\n    param($Element, $Invariants)\r\n    \r\n    $isInvariant = $false\r\n    \r\n    if ($Element -match 'Phase \\d' -or $Element -match 'COMPLETE|Active|Pending') { $isInvariant = $true }\r\n    if ($Element -match '\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}' -or $Element -match 'pulse_\\d{14}') { $isInvariant = $false } # Timestamps are variant\r\n    if ($Element -match '^-\\s+\\[') { $\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:29:40\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774355571114}}
